heaviest_rainfall.status: The heaviest total rainfall occurred on 04 January 2025, dropping 36.8mm of rain over the 37.2 hour storm duration with a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 16.2mm per hour was the peak rain rate recorded today ranking 4th in our overall records.  The storm lasted 6.9 hours and 9.36mm of rain fell.  The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: The lengthiest precipitation event recorded spanned 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025, it was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 4.6mm per hour and a total rainfall of 36.8mm.

most_lightning.status: Since records began on 11 April 2025, the highest lightning strike count in one day is 23 on 07 September 2025.

nearest_lightning.status: The closest strike happened on 13 May 2025, a distance of just 4.97 miles away.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 2.6°C), outside temperature (down 2.3°C), and inside temperature (down 1.8°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 8%).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 649 m) and light levels (up 5523 lux).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1247 m), light levels (up 7458 lux), and rainfall (down 0.5 mm) when compared to today.
